programme.title: Tottenham Hotspur vs. Manchester City - English Premier League 2026/2027
programme.desc: Man City’s Antoine Semenyo has scored five goals in his last eight Premier League appearances, the joint most of any player in that timeframe. One of those was a late winner against Spurs for Bournemouth in January, with only Eric Cantona in 1992-93 and Benito Carbone in 1999-00 scoring against Spurs for two teams in a single season. Omar Marmoush netted his first Premier League goal of the season in Man City’s 2-0 win over Wolves but all eight of his goals in the competition have been scored at home – he’s failed to score with all 20 of his attempts in 12 games away from home.

Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.
